I am sharing my notes on Egyptian mythology for those that which to use them
https://www.sofurry.com/view/2074670

And for the rest of you I will tell you the story of the Memphis Egyptian Pantheon, and how the creator of all, got married.

So, many years ago, when the great red desert we call the Sahara was as green and as luscious as the banks of the line itself, the maker of all, Ptah, gave the role of his Eye to Hathor, goddess of love. Ptah, going about to create the other four realms of his divine kingdom, was blind to the fact that the ever-loyal Hathor had grown enraged seeing the cruelty of life, and particularly, mankind. She saw adultery, murder, and much worse from the heavens. One day her anger to the better of her, and burned into a new level and she descended from the heavens and her body, that the most beautiful woman, had merged with that of a lioness, with blade and claw she started her rampage across the earth in an effort to wipe out all life. Forests were hacked away with a single swing, cities, herds, and wild beasts were slaughtered indiscriminately and their blood pooled in massive lakes that this new goddess of war would drink in thirsty gulps. This new goddess, Sekhmet boiled away Hathor back into the heavens, where Hathor ran to Ptah and Thoth to ask for help to sate the rage of Sekhmet. Thoth gave Ptah an idea, to make a lake of fake blood to get Sekhmet into a drunken stupor, where she could be brought back into the heavens. So with the advice of Thoth, Ptah created a great lake of blood red beer from 7000 barrels of it near where the city of Memphis is today. When Sekhmet arrived, she drank the whole lake not even realizing she hadn't slaughtered the people and fell asleep drunk. Then Ptah scooped her up and took her home to the heavens. Unsure of who to give the role of his eye to, Ptah elected to allow Hathor to remain his eye and made Sekhmet his consort as make them equal.
That's why the Sahara exists the rage of a lioness goddess
